text: Veena Devi is a politician from Bihar and a member of the BJP. She is the wife of Dinesh Prasad Singh, an ex MLA from Gaighat, Bihar. She became an MLA in the Vidhan Sabha election in 2010 in Gaighat with the alliance of BJP. She had contested the 2010 Vidhan Sabha elections from Ghaighat Seat on the BJP ticket. She was ex Chairperson from Muzaffarpur and ex Vice Chairperson from Muzaffarpur. She is the wife of Dinesh Prasad Singh, who is Janata Dal (United) MLC and chairman of Vidhan Parishad from Muzaffarpur, who had a record win in MLC elections in Bihar.Her daughter in law is the current chairperson of Muzaffarpur.

text: Vishnu Savara (Born on the date of 1 June 1950 to Smt. Yashoda Savara & Shri. Rama Savara, who belong to a family of Farmers residing at Village-Galtare, Wada an area under Palghar District) is a leader of Bharatiya Janata Party. He is a Cabinet Minister for Tribal Development  in Government of Maharashtra. He was elected to Maharashtra Legislative Assembly from Wada (ST) constituency in 1990,1995,1999,2004. In 2009, after delimitation he contested assembly election from Bhiwandi Rural (Vidhan Sabha constituency) (ST) reservation and won. In 2014 assembly Election he contest from Vikramgad (Vidhan Sabha constituency) seat and won.

text: Vitthalrao Gadgil (1928–2001) was a leader of Indian National Congress. He was a member of Lok Sabha elected from Pune. He was member of the Rajya Sabha from 1971 to 1980 and from 1994 to 2000 and of the Lok Sabha from 1980 to 1991. He served as union minister of information and broadcasting.
